import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['lat'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitudes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    avg_lat = data['lat'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(avg_lat, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Average Latitude: {avg_lat:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average latitude in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['key'] = pd.to_numeric(data['key'], errors='coerce')
    min_key = data['key'].min()
    max_key = data['key'].max()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['key'], bins=20, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(min_key, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Min Key: {min_key:.2f}')
    ax.axvline(max_key, color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Max Key: {max_key:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the range of keys in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
